<subSubSection id="C37B6575C45D7C3ADA85FE39B9BAFDE6" pageId="2" pageNumber="148" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BDE36FEC45D7C3ADA85FE39B9BAFDE6" blockId="2.[136,779,379,924]" pageId="2" pageNumber="148">
<emphasis id="B915EAECC45D7C3ADA85FE39BA59FE58" bold="true" box="[189,324,417,443]" pageId="2" pageNumber="148">Etymology.</emphasis>
The generic name is an anagram of 
<taxonomicName id="4C614D7DC45D7C3ADA87FE5EBA6FFE03" authorityName="Curtis" authorityYear="1833" box="[191,370,454,480]" class="Insecta" family="Endomychidae" genus="Holoparamecus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B915EAECC45D7C3ADA87FE5EBA6FFE03" box="[191,370,454,480]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="148">Holoparamecus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a genus in 
<taxonomicName id="4C614D7DC45D7C3AD862FE5EB81AFE03" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[602,775,454,480]" class="Insecta" family="Endomychidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Endomychidae</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C614D7DC45D7C3ADAB0FE73BA29FDE6" authorityName="Seidlitz" authorityYear="1872" box="[136,308,491,517]" class="Insecta" family="Endomychidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Merophysiinae">Merophysiinae</taxonomicName>
. The name is feminine in gender.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37B6575C45D7C3ADA85FD97BAF4FC7F" pageId="2" pageNumber="148" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BDE36FEC45D7C3ADA85FD97BAF4FC7F" blockId="2.[136,779,379,924]" pageId="2" pageNumber="148">
<emphasis id="B915EAECC45D7C3ADA85FD97BA25FDCA" bold="true" box="[189,312,527,553]" pageId="2" pageNumber="148">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body relatively elongate. Head with antennal sockets visible from above (
<figureCitation id="135A2A7BC45D7C3AD808FDADB996FDAC" box="[560,651,564,591]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="5.[136,235,1428,1452]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,189,1405]" captionTargetId="figure-217@5.[151,1436,189,1405]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 5. X-ray microtomographic reconstruction of Rhomeocalpsua torosa Li, Tomaszewska &amp; Cai, gen. et sp. nov., holotype, NIGP180054. A, Dorsal view. B, Ventral view. C, Anterodorsal view. D, Lateral view. E, Posterior view. F, Antenna, rendered under “Sum along Ray” mode. Scale bars = 500 μm in A–E, 200 μm in F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530517" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530517/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="148">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
). Antennae composed of nine antennomeres, with club built of three antennomeres; antennomere 7 strongly asymmetrical; antennomere 8 strongly enlarged (
<figureCitation id="135A2A7BC45D7C3AD83CFD3CB99FFD5D" box="[516,642,676,702]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[136,235,1533,1557]" captionTargetBox="[145,1443,198,1509]" captionTargetId="figure-132@4.[145,1443,198,1509]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Details of Rhomeocalpsua torosa Li, Tomaszewska &amp; Cai, gen. et sp. nov., holotype, NIGP180054, under confocal microscopy. A, Head, dorsal view. B, Head, ventral view. C, Antenna, dorsal view. D, Antenna, ventral view. E, Mesothorax, ventral view. F, Abdominal base, ventral view. G, Abdominal apex, ventral view. H, Mesotarsus, ventral view. I, Metatarsus, dorsal view. Abbreviations: a1–9, antennomeres 1–9; cl, clypeus; lbp, labial palp; msc, mesocoxa; msf, mesofemur; mst1–3, mesotarsomeres 1–3; msv, mesoventrite; mtf, metafemur; mtt1–3, metatarsomeres 1–3; mtv, metaventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; v1–6, ventrites 1–6. Scale bars = 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530513" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530513/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="148">Figs 4C, D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="135A2A7BC45D7C3AD8B4FD3BB9B0FD5D" box="[652,685,675,702]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="5.[136,235,1428,1452]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,189,1405]" captionTargetId="figure-217@5.[151,1436,189,1405]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 5. X-ray microtomographic reconstruction of Rhomeocalpsua torosa Li, Tomaszewska &amp; Cai, gen. et sp. nov., holotype, NIGP180054. A, Dorsal view. B, Ventral view. C, Anterodorsal view. D, Lateral view. E, Posterior view. F, Antenna, rendered under “Sum along Ray” mode. Scale bars = 500 μm in A–E, 200 μm in F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530517" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530517/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="148">5F</figureCitation>
). Apical labial palpomeres apparently enlarged (
<figureCitation id="135A2A7BC45D7C3AD80DFD51B997FD00" box="[565,650,713,739]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[136,235,1533,1557]" captionTargetBox="[145,1443,198,1509]" captionTargetId="figure-132@4.[145,1443,198,1509]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Details of Rhomeocalpsua torosa Li, Tomaszewska &amp; Cai, gen. et sp. nov., holotype, NIGP180054, under confocal microscopy. A, Head, dorsal view. B, Head, ventral view. C, Antenna, dorsal view. D, Antenna, ventral view. E, Mesothorax, ventral view. F, Abdominal base, ventral view. G, Abdominal apex, ventral view. H, Mesotarsus, ventral view. I, Metatarsus, dorsal view. Abbreviations: a1–9, antennomeres 1–9; cl, clypeus; lbp, labial palp; msc, mesocoxa; msf, mesofemur; mst1–3, mesotarsomeres 1–3; msv, mesoventrite; mtf, metafemur; mtt1–3, metatarsomeres 1–3; mtv, metaventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; v1–6, ventrites 1–6. Scale bars = 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530513" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530513/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="148">Fig.4B</figureCitation>
). Prothorax posteriorly constricted; pronotal disc without pits, sulci or carinae (
<figureCitation id="135A2A7BC45D7C3ADB34FC8BBA74FCCE" box="[268,361,787,813]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[136,235,1157,1181]" captionTargetBox="[215,1372,189,1134]" captionTargetId="figure-312@3.[215,1372,189,1134]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. General habitus of Rhomeocalpsua torosa Li, Tomaszewska &amp; Cai, gen. et sp. nov., holotype, NIGP180054, under confocal microscopy. A, Dorsal view. B, Ventral view. Scale bars = 500 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530511" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530511/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="148">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Mesocoxal cavities broadly closed (
<figureCitation id="135A2A7BC45D7C3ADAA8FCA0BBF7FCB1" box="[144,234,824,850]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[136,235,1533,1557]" captionTargetBox="[145,1443,198,1509]" captionTargetId="figure-132@4.[145,1443,198,1509]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Details of Rhomeocalpsua torosa Li, Tomaszewska &amp; Cai, gen. et sp. nov., holotype, NIGP180054, under confocal microscopy. A, Head, dorsal view. B, Head, ventral view. C, Antenna, dorsal view. D, Antenna, ventral view. E, Mesothorax, ventral view. F, Abdominal base, ventral view. G, Abdominal apex, ventral view. H, Mesotarsus, ventral view. I, Metatarsus, dorsal view. Abbreviations: a1–9, antennomeres 1–9; cl, clypeus; lbp, labial palp; msc, mesocoxa; msf, mesofemur; mst1–3, mesotarsomeres 1–3; msv, mesoventrite; mtf, metafemur; mtt1–3, metatarsomeres 1–3; mtv, metaventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; v1–6, ventrites 1–6. Scale bars = 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530513" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530513/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="148">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
). Mesotrochantins concealed (
<figureCitation id="135A2A7BC45D7C3AD87DFCA0B982FCB1" box="[581,671,824,850]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[136,235,1533,1557]" captionTargetBox="[145,1443,198,1509]" captionTargetId="figure-132@4.[145,1443,198,1509]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Details of Rhomeocalpsua torosa Li, Tomaszewska &amp; Cai, gen. et sp. nov., holotype, NIGP180054, under confocal microscopy. A, Head, dorsal view. B, Head, ventral view. C, Antenna, dorsal view. D, Antenna, ventral view. E, Mesothorax, ventral view. F, Abdominal base, ventral view. G, Abdominal apex, ventral view. H, Mesotarsus, ventral view. I, Metatarsus, dorsal view. Abbreviations: a1–9, antennomeres 1–9; cl, clypeus; lbp, labial palp; msc, mesocoxa; msf, mesofemur; mst1–3, mesotarsomeres 1–3; msv, mesoventrite; mtf, metafemur; mtt1–3, metatarsomeres 1–3; mtv, metaventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; v1–6, ventrites 1–6. Scale bars = 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530513" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530513/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="148">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
). Femora with deep and long grooves along inner side (
<figureCitation id="135A2A7BC45D7C3AD8B0FCC5B9E0FC94" box="[648,765,861,887]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[136,235,1533,1557]" captionTargetBox="[145,1443,198,1509]" captionTargetId="figure-132@4.[145,1443,198,1509]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Details of Rhomeocalpsua torosa Li, Tomaszewska &amp; Cai, gen. et sp. nov., holotype, NIGP180054, under confocal microscopy. A, Head, dorsal view. B, Head, ventral view. C, Antenna, dorsal view. D, Antenna, ventral view. E, Mesothorax, ventral view. F, Abdominal base, ventral view. G, Abdominal apex, ventral view. H, Mesotarsus, ventral view. I, Metatarsus, dorsal view. Abbreviations: a1–9, antennomeres 1–9; cl, clypeus; lbp, labial palp; msc, mesocoxa; msf, mesofemur; mst1–3, mesotarsomeres 1–3; msv, mesoventrite; mtf, metafemur; mtt1–3, metatarsomeres 1–3; mtv, metaventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; v1–6, ventrites 1–6. Scale bars = 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530513" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530513/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="148">Fig. 4E, F</figureCitation>
). Tarsi simple, 3-3-3 (
<figureCitation id="135A2A7BC45D7C3ADB53FC1ABAC6FC7F" box="[363,475,898,924]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[136,235,1533,1557]" captionTargetBox="[145,1443,198,1509]" captionTargetId="figure-132@4.[145,1443,198,1509]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Details of Rhomeocalpsua torosa Li, Tomaszewska &amp; Cai, gen. et sp. nov., holotype, NIGP180054, under confocal microscopy. A, Head, dorsal view. B, Head, ventral view. C, Antenna, dorsal view. D, Antenna, ventral view. E, Mesothorax, ventral view. F, Abdominal base, ventral view. G, Abdominal apex, ventral view. H, Mesotarsus, ventral view. I, Metatarsus, dorsal view. Abbreviations: a1–9, antennomeres 1–9; cl, clypeus; lbp, labial palp; msc, mesocoxa; msf, mesofemur; mst1–3, mesotarsomeres 1–3; msv, mesoventrite; mtf, metafemur; mtt1–3, metatarsomeres 1–3; mtv, metaventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; v1–6, ventrites 1–6. Scale bars = 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530513" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530513/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="148">Fig. 4H, I</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
